  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Peel and dice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;finely&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dice the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-size pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pour 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> onto a baking tray and add half the <strong>curry powder</strong> (you'll use the rest later)</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to the spiced oil and mix to coat them evenly, then&nbsp;put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the potatoes are crispy - these are your <strong>spiced potatoes</strong>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>lamb mince</strong> with the remaining <strong>curry powder</strong>, 1/3 of the<strong>&nbsp;diced onion</strong>, half the <strong>chopped&nbsp;ginger</strong> and half the <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later)</p>\r\n<p>Season the mix with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and plenty of <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix well with clean hands, divide into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span>&nbsp;<strong>patties</strong> and refrigerate until step 6</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a small pot with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the remaining <strong>diced&nbsp;onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the onion has softened</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>diced</strong>&nbsp;<strong>tomato</strong>, remaining <strong>chopped&nbsp;ginger</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong>, half the <strong>white wine&nbsp;</strong><strong>vinegar</strong> (keep the rest for step 7) and cook for 10-12 min or until reduced to a chutney-like consistency</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the<strong> brioche rolls</strong>&nbsp;in half</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, dry wide-based pan (or griddle if you have one!) over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>brioche</strong>, cut-side-down and toast them for 3 min or until coloured</p>\r\n<p>Once toasted, set them<strong>&nbsp;</strong>aside until serving, reserving the pan</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/434.step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
